---
description: Designing or modifying AWS infrastructure, choosing between AWS services, configuring Lambda functions, or working with DynamoDB and template.yaml
alwaysApply: false
---
# AWS & Cost

- If a suggestion would incur AWS cost beyond the free tier, flag it explicitly
  and offer a free alternative.
- Never suggest RDS, SageMaker, ElastiCache, or NAT Gateways.
- All infrastructure is defined in `template.yaml` (AWS SAM). If new AWS resources
  are needed, add them there — never suggest console-only solutions.
- Lambda memory should stay at 512 MB unless there is a clear, justified reason
  to increase it.
- DynamoDB access should use on-demand capacity mode in dev. All access goes
  through repository classes — no raw SDK calls in handler or service code.
- AWS SDK clients are instantiated only in repository or service constructors,
  never in handlers.